            <scopecontent id="aspace_c60a2774f7a07f0cc376c9c903739afe">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Contains correspondence and other papers dated 1801-1802 relating to a cancelled expedition to Louisiana, and papers concerning the voyage of Captain Pierre Bernard Milius to Île Bourbon (now Réunion). Also included are correspondence and reports about horticulture in Cayenne, French Guiana, and plants from Europe and other countries that could be cultivated in a French settlement in Senegal.</p>
